'''Dina Perbellini''' (14 January, 1901–2 April, 1984) was an Italian [[actress]]. She appeared in over sixty films and television series between 1934 and 1969 and was also a leading [[voice actress]], dubbing foreign films for release in Italy. She made her film debut in the 1934 school comedy ''[[Seconda B]]''.<ref>Reich & Garofalo p.154</ref>

